This paper is about knowledge base population, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract structured information from unstructured text. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses methods for improving the precision and recall of relation extraction, which are core topics in machine learning (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DB). The paper also uses techniques such as feature labeling and semantic label propagation, which are related to graph-based algorithms and dimensionality reduction, respectively, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
